By providing vehicle insurance discounts based on the results of a digital driving test, the app also helps customers save money. The app soft-launched recently in both the Google Play and Apple App stores, with an official launch set for next month. Some of the features include quick and easy claims registration and tracking, digital sales and electronic vehicle inspection. * Georgina Crouth is a consumer watchdog with serious bite. Write to her at consumer@inl.co.za, tweet her @georginacrouth and follow her on Facebook.